  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Creating Models of Ethical Recruitment Practices in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a global leader in promoting ethical recruitment, IOM will engage key stakeholders in Bangladesh&apos;s overseas labor recruitment industry to adopt the necessary industry reform towards new business models that encourage ethical practices. The project will support committed ethical recruitment agencies to achieve self-sustainability and scalability by establishing linkages with like-minded employers in destination countries and exploring business relationships in new safe migration corridors. The project will additionally engage with other interested recruitment agencies and provide them with training, tools and support to shift towards ethical recruitment practices through the International Recruitment Integrity System (IRIS) Labour Recruiter Capacity Building Programme. The project will also help to raise awareness of ethical recruitment among communities, sub-agents and second- and third-tier recruitment agencies through targeted community-level engagement in Cumilla, Dhaka and Noakhali. It will also encourage the formalization of sub-agents through established business relationships with licensed recruitment agencies and their sub-offices.</narrative>
  </description>
